253
00:18:53,000 --> 00:18:55,116
MAGGlE: I'm taking no chances
on moving you.

254
00:18:55,200 --> 00:18:56,189
I won't break.

255
00:18:56,280 --> 00:18:59,750
Or letting them poison
Big Daddy's mind against you.

256
00:19:00,400 --> 00:19:04,359
I just want you to get dressed
and come to Big Daddy's birthday party.

257
00:19:04,640 --> 00:19:07,837
First thing Big Daddy asked about was you.

258
00:19:08,040 --> 00:19:10,600
Big Daddy! Now what makes him so big?

259
00:19:11,240 --> 00:19:13,549
His big heart, his big belly...

260
00:19:13,760 --> 00:19:14,988
...or his big money?

261
00:19:16,280 --> 00:19:18,430
MAGGlE: The heat has made you cross.

262
00:19:18,600 --> 00:19:20,158
Give me my crutch.

263
00:19:22,680 --> 00:19:24,989
Why don't you put on
your silk pajamas, honey...

264
00:19:25,200 --> 00:19:27,111
...and come on down to the party?

265
00:19:27,320 --> 00:19:29,515
There's a lovely cool breeze.

266
00:19:30,200 --> 00:19:32,031
Give me my crutch, Maggie.

267
00:19:33,200 --> 00:19:35,316
Lean on me, baby.

268
00:19:35,720 --> 00:19:37,711
[Slow instrumental music]

269
00:19:41,800 --> 00:19:44,439
You've got a nice smell about you.

270
00:19:46,120 --> 00:19:48,680
-Was your bathwater cool?
-No.

271
00:19:50,360 --> 00:19:53,557
I know something
that would make you cool and fresh.

272
00:19:54,440 --> 00:19:56,032
Alcohol rub.

273
00:19:56,680 --> 00:19:57,954
Cologne.

274
00:19:58,760 --> 00:20:00,239
No thanks. We'd smell alike.

275
00:20:00,320 --> 00:20:02,788
Like a couple of cats in the heat.

276
00:20:12,600 --> 00:20:14,272
It's cool on the lawn.

277
00:20:14,480 --> 00:20:18,553
I am not going down there.
Not for you and not for Big Daddy!

278
00:20:21,320 --> 00:20:23,197
At least give him this present...

279
00:20:23,400 --> 00:20:26,790
...that I remembered to buy for you,
for his birthday.

280
00:20:27,400 --> 00:20:29,231
Just write a few words on this card.

281
00:20:29,440 --> 00:20:30,919
You write something.

282
00:20:31,120 --> 00:20:34,556
It's got to be your handwriting.
It's your present.

283
00:20:34,760 --> 00:20:36,113
I didn't get him a present.

284
00:20:36,320 --> 00:20:37,548
What's the difference?

285
00:20:37,760 --> 00:20:39,830
If there's no difference, you write the card!

286
00:20:39,920 --> 00:20:42,753
-And have him know you didn't remember?
-I didn't remember!

287
00:20:42,920 --> 00:20:44,876
You don't have to prove it to him!

288
00:20:45,080 --> 00:20:47,150
Just write, "Love, Brick"...

289
00:20:47,360 --> 00:20:48,509
-...for heaven's sake!
-No.

290
00:20:48,680 --> 00:20:51,558
-You've got to.
-I don't have to do anything!

291
00:20:51,760 --> 00:20:54,877
You forget the conditions I agreed on
to stay living with you!

292
00:20:54,960 --> 00:20:58,919
I'm not living with you.
We occupy the same cage, that's all!

293
00:21:00,200 --> 00:21:02,191
[Slow instrumental music]

294
00:21:06,920 --> 00:21:11,232
That's the first time you've raised
your voice in a long time.

295
00:21:13,920 --> 00:21:15,353
A crack in the stone wall?

296
00:21:21,200 --> 00:21:23,873
MAGGlE: I think that's a fine sign.
Mighty fine.

297
00:21:29,360 --> 00:21:30,554
What did you do that for?

298
00:21:34,440 --> 00:21:37,000
To give us a little privacy for a while.

299
00:21:38,080 --> 00:21:39,911
BRlCK: Don't make a fool of yourself.

300
00:21:43,800 --> 00:21:46,439
I don't mind making a fool
of myself over you.

301
00:21:46,600 --> 00:21:49,068
I mind. I feel embarrassed for you.

302
00:21:49,480 --> 00:21:50,833
Feel embarrassed!

303
00:21:51,720 --> 00:21:52,835
I can't live on this way.

304
00:21:53,000 --> 00:21:56,913
-You agreed to accept that condition!
-I know I did, but I can't!

305
00:21:59,120 --> 00:22:00,269
BRlCK: Let go.

306
00:22:06,440 --> 00:22:08,158
Let go, Maggie!

307
00:22:25,360 --> 00:22:26,588
BlG MAMA: Son!

308
00:22:29,080 --> 00:22:31,674
We've got the most wonderful news
about Big Daddy!

309
00:22:31,840 --> 00:22:33,990
BlG MAMA: What's this door doing locked?

310
00:22:34,160 --> 00:22:36,196
You think there's robbers in the house?

311
00:22:37,320 --> 00:22:39,197
Brick's getting dressed, Big Mama.

312
00:22:39,400 --> 00:22:40,674
He's still getting dressed.

313
00:22:40,840 --> 00:22:43,877
BlG MAMA: It won't be the first time
I've seen Brick not dressed.

314
00:22:44,000 --> 00:22:45,274
Open this door.

315
00:22:46,640 --> 00:22:48,710
[Banging on door]

316
00:22:55,000 --> 00:22:56,353
BlG MAMA: Brick, honey!

317
00:22:56,520 --> 00:22:58,238
Sweetheart, how does your leg feel?

318
00:22:58,440 --> 00:23:01,477
Come out of there. I want to give you
the news about Big Daddy.

319
00:23:01,640 --> 00:23:03,676
I told him already.

320
00:23:03,880 --> 00:23:05,791
I just hate locked doors in the house.

321
00:23:06,000 --> 00:23:09,436
MAGGlE: I know you do
but people need privacy, don't they?

322
00:23:09,640 --> 00:23:11,710
No, ma'am, not in my house.

323
00:23:11,880 --> 00:23:14,952
What did you take this off for?
It looked so sweet on you.

324
00:23:15,080 --> 00:23:17,719
MAGGlE: Not sweet enough
for Big Daddy's birthday party.

325
00:23:17,840 --> 00:23:18,829
[Whistle blows]

326
00:23:19,200 --> 00:23:20,189
Out!

327
00:23:21,640 --> 00:23:22,755
Out, you little monster!

328
00:23:30,080 --> 00:23:33,311
Mae and Gooper are so touchy
about their children.

329
00:23:33,480 --> 00:23:37,268
You hardly even dare suggest
there's any room for improvement.

330
00:23:37,480 --> 00:23:38,959
Brick, hurry on out!

331
00:23:39,160 --> 00:23:41,958
Shoot, Maggie, you just don't like children.

332
00:23:42,160 --> 00:23:44,628
Why that's not true. I adore them.

333
00:23:44,840 --> 00:23:45,955
Well brought up.

334
00:23:46,120 --> 00:23:48,429
Why not have some, then,
and bring them up well?

335
00:23:48,520 --> 00:23:51,353
BlG MAMA: lnstead of picking on theirs?
GOOPER: Big Mama!

336
00:23:51,560 --> 00:23:54,438
Hugh and Betsy have got to go.
They're waiting to say goodbye.

337
00:23:54,520 --> 00:23:57,193
I'll be right down.
Tell them to hold their horses.

338
00:23:58,760 --> 00:23:59,636
Where's Brick?

339
00:24:05,520 --> 00:24:06,999
Oh.

340
00:24:09,040 --> 00:24:11,713
What you said about having children....

341
00:24:11,880 --> 00:24:13,871
It's still kind of a secret, but--

342
00:24:15,440 --> 00:24:18,273
Shoot, Maggie! Stop playing so dumb.

343
00:24:18,560 --> 00:24:20,551
Is he still drinking this stuff much?

344
00:24:22,160 --> 00:24:24,993
-He may have had a little highball.
-Don't laugh about it.

345
00:24:25,200 --> 00:24:28,112
Some men stop drinking when they marry.
Others start.

346
00:24:28,320 --> 00:24:30,276
-He never drank before--
-That's not fair!

347
00:24:30,360 --> 00:24:32,828
Fair or not, I want to ask you a question.

348
00:24:33,440 --> 00:24:34,839
Do you make Brick happy?

349
00:24:35,960 --> 00:24:37,279
Well?

350
00:24:39,160 --> 00:24:40,912
Why don't you ask if he makes me happy?

351
00:24:41,000 --> 00:24:42,194
BlG MAMA: I know--

352
00:24:42,280 --> 00:24:43,269
It works both ways.

353
00:24:43,360 --> 00:24:47,592
Something ain't right.
You're childless and my son drinks.

354
00:24:47,800 --> 00:24:50,473
GOOPER: We're leaving, Big Mama.
BlG MAMA: I'm coming!

355
00:24:50,720 --> 00:24:52,756
When a marriage goes on the rocks...

356
00:24:52,960 --> 00:24:55,554
...the rocks are there, right there!

357
00:24:55,760 --> 00:24:57,159
MAN'S VOlCE: Goodbye, lda.

358
00:24:57,240 --> 00:24:58,798
I'm coming.

359
00:25:04,720 --> 00:25:06,711
That's not fair.

360
00:25:07,080 --> 00:25:08,911
All right, I'm coming.

361
00:25:11,640 --> 00:25:13,039
[Knock on door]

362
00:25:13,480 --> 00:25:15,152
DR. BAUGH: Is Brick here?

363
00:25:15,840 --> 00:25:18,115
I thought I'd check his ankle.

364
00:25:18,680 --> 00:25:20,033
Is it giving him much pain?

365
00:25:20,240 --> 00:25:23,550
You know how Brick is, Doc.
He hardly ever complains.

366
00:25:23,720 --> 00:25:27,315
Even when he had
that awful back injury in football.

367
00:25:27,440 --> 00:25:29,078
DR. BAUGH: Brick!

368
00:25:29,200 --> 00:25:31,589
Brick's birthday present for Big Daddy.

369
00:25:32,600 --> 00:25:35,194
I think they're fixing
to sit down at the table.

370
00:25:39,640 --> 00:25:42,632
You forgot to write out the card, honey.

371
00:25:45,640 --> 00:25:46,675
Thanks, Doc.

372
00:25:53,760 --> 00:25:55,079
Can I get you something cool?

373
00:25:55,840 --> 00:25:56,829
No, thanks.

374
00:25:57,240 --> 00:25:58,958
How's the ankle?

375
00:26:01,640 --> 00:26:03,232
Itches some.

376
00:26:04,040 --> 00:26:07,510
Funny, that's the same leg
you tore a muscle in the....

377
00:26:07,920 --> 00:26:09,148
'Bama State.

378
00:26:09,360 --> 00:26:10,793
Twenty-one to--

379
00:26:11,000 --> 00:26:11,671
Nothing.

380
00:26:11,880 --> 00:26:14,030
You miss football, don't you?

381
00:26:14,240 --> 00:26:16,037
Hurt much when you put weight on it?

382
00:26:16,200 --> 00:26:17,189
Some.

383
00:26:17,400 --> 00:26:20,870
Yeah, you were quite a team,
you and Skipper.

384
00:26:23,240 --> 00:26:24,832
What is it, Doc?

385
00:26:25,120 --> 00:26:28,396
You didn't leave that party
to come up and discuss my health.

386
00:26:28,880 --> 00:26:29,596
That's right.

387
00:26:29,680 --> 00:26:32,911
BRlCK: I've already heard the good news--
DR. BAUGH: It's bad news.

388
00:26:33,000 --> 00:26:34,956
It's what we expected.

389
00:26:35,320 --> 00:26:37,436
It's malignant and it's terminal.

390
00:26:37,640 --> 00:26:39,517
He hasn't a chance.

391
00:26:39,720 --> 00:26:42,678
BRlCK: But Maggie said, and Big Mama--
DR. BAUGH: Lies.

392
00:26:43,240 --> 00:26:44,468
I lied to them.

393
00:26:45,400 --> 00:26:47,595
I lied to him, too.

394
00:26:48,880 --> 00:26:49,835
Professional ethics.

395
00:26:51,560 --> 00:26:52,072
Gooper?

396
00:26:52,280 --> 00:26:54,794
I told him the truth
coming in from the airfield.

397
00:26:55,400 --> 00:26:56,549
He's going to die.

398
00:26:58,360 --> 00:26:59,839
He's going to die.

399
00:27:01,240 --> 00:27:03,834
[Children singing]

400
00:27:08,360 --> 00:27:11,397
CHlLDREN: [Sing]
"Jesus wants me for a sunbeam"

401
00:27:14,040 --> 00:27:16,349
What kind of truth is that?

402
00:27:34,920 --> 00:27:37,832
CHlLDREN: [Sing]
"Jesus wants me for a sunbeam

403
00:27:38,040 --> 00:27:40,474
"To shine for him each day

404
00:27:41,840 --> 00:27:44,832
"ln every way try to please him

405
00:27:45,040 --> 00:27:47,554
"At home, at school, at play

406
00:27:48,360 --> 00:27:49,793
"A sunbeam

407
00:27:51,960 --> 00:27:54,758
"Jesus wants me for a sunbeam

408
00:27:55,240 --> 00:27:57,834
"A sunbeam, a sunbeam

409
00:27:58,280 --> 00:28:00,999
"I'll be a sunbeam for him"

410
00:28:01,280 --> 00:28:02,599
DEACON: Amen!

411
00:28:02,720 --> 00:28:05,871
MAE: Did you like the singing?
BlG DADDY: Pass the black-eyed peas.

412
00:28:06,000 --> 00:28:09,549
BlG MAMA: Look at Big Daddy eat!
Ain't it something to thank your stars for?

413
00:28:09,720 --> 00:28:11,950
They've been practicing just for you.

414
00:28:12,040 --> 00:28:13,234
Tell them to sit and eat.

415
00:28:13,320 --> 00:28:15,197
-Children, come on.
-Over there!

416
00:28:15,400 --> 00:28:17,311
Yeah. Over there.

417
00:28:18,160 --> 00:28:19,559
Look here. Telegrams!

418
00:28:19,640 --> 00:28:22,279
Hundreds of them from every corner
of this great state--

419
00:28:22,400 --> 00:28:23,913
GOOPER: Wishing you happy birthday.

420
00:28:24,040 --> 00:28:25,917
BlG MAMA: Shall I read them?
BlG DADDY: No!

421
00:28:26,000 --> 00:28:27,797
One from the governor and the senator--

422
00:28:27,880 --> 00:28:30,917
It must be getting on to election time,
hey, Deacon?

423
00:28:31,080 --> 00:28:33,674
Let's remember,
we're all lambs in the same pasture.

424
00:28:33,880 --> 00:28:37,634
Everybody, including Big Daddy,
owes thanks to those in high places who--

425
00:28:37,840 --> 00:28:38,909
Gave us nothing!

426
00:28:39,080 --> 00:28:42,959
Every scrap on this table was raised
right here on this place, Deacon.

427
00:28:43,160 --> 00:28:47,358
I made a pastureland out of this place
when it was nothing but a swamp.

428
00:28:47,560 --> 00:28:50,632
And it was done with the help of God,
and not any governor.

429
00:28:50,720 --> 00:28:51,391
Amen.

430
00:28:51,480 --> 00:28:53,914
CHlLDREN: [Sing]
"Boom, boom and it makes me crazy"

431
00:28:54,000 --> 00:28:55,228
Great balls of fire!

432
00:28:55,440 --> 00:28:56,589
Surprise!

433
00:28:56,800 --> 00:28:59,712
-What are they up to now?
-It's part of the entertainment.

434
00:28:59,880 --> 00:29:01,711
Don't they get any intermission?

435
00:29:01,920 --> 00:29:03,399
That's funny!

436
00:29:03,880 --> 00:29:05,233
GOOPER: That's very funny!

437
00:29:05,440 --> 00:29:07,590
He don't mean it, Sister Woman.

438
00:29:07,720 --> 00:29:10,314
BlG MAMA: He loves children!
GOOPER: Of course he does!

439
00:29:10,440 --> 00:29:12,351
Will you put some honey on this?

440
00:29:12,560 --> 00:29:15,552
They're all Pollitts,
I'm proud to say, every one of them.

441
00:29:15,760 --> 00:29:18,354
I know Big Daddy's
just as proud as we are...

442
00:29:18,560 --> 00:29:20,676
...that there's a flesh-and-blood dynasty...

443
00:29:20,840 --> 00:29:22,990
...waiting to take over.

444
00:29:23,200 --> 00:29:25,191
That's no way to talk.

445
00:29:25,400 --> 00:29:26,196
What way?

446
00:29:26,400 --> 00:29:30,279
MAGGlE: "Take over." When we all know...

447
00:29:30,480 --> 00:29:32,835
...Big Daddy's going to live
to be at least 100.

448
00:29:32,920 --> 00:29:34,478
I'll drink to that!

449
00:29:34,840 --> 00:29:36,910
Anytime, anyplace, anywhere!

450
00:29:37,120 --> 00:29:38,553
To Big Daddy!

451
00:29:38,640 --> 00:29:40,153
[Children continue singing]

452
00:29:40,240 --> 00:29:43,152
DEACON: In the name of every person
in this county...

453
00:29:43,240 --> 00:29:46,630
...in the name of the church
and school board, the board of trustees...

454
00:29:46,720 --> 00:29:49,393
...felicitations on your 65th birthday.

455
00:29:50,600 --> 00:29:52,750
Brick, honey,
I brought you something to eat.

456
00:29:52,960 --> 00:29:54,439
BRlCK: I'm not hungry.

457
00:29:57,800 --> 00:29:59,756
What's that supposed to mean?

458
00:29:59,960 --> 00:30:01,154
BRlCK: We're leaving.

459
00:30:01,280 --> 00:30:02,952
MAGGlE: We can't.
BRlCK: I can.

460
00:30:03,080 --> 00:30:06,550
-The party's coming up here to you.
-I'll get one of the boys to drive me.

461
00:30:06,680 --> 00:30:10,309
You just can't walk out
on Big Daddy's birthday party!

462
00:30:10,520 --> 00:30:12,158
Don't you care nothing about him?

463
00:30:12,240 --> 00:30:13,639
Get out of my way.

464
00:30:14,760 --> 00:30:17,035
Get out of my way, Maggie!

465
00:30:19,520 --> 00:30:21,317
You've got no cause to dislike him.

466
00:30:23,560 --> 00:30:24,879
Do I dislike him?

467
00:30:25,080 --> 00:30:28,959
It's obvious to everybody.
Especially to him.

468
00:30:32,960 --> 00:30:34,518
What's he ever done to you?

469
00:30:34,720 --> 00:30:35,709
What?

470
00:30:35,920 --> 00:30:38,070
Why do you hate him so much?

471
00:30:38,440 --> 00:30:39,793
What's he ever done to you?

472
00:30:43,560 --> 00:30:44,276
Nothing.

473
00:30:45,800 --> 00:30:48,234
What was Dr. Baugh doing up here?

474
00:30:49,600 --> 00:30:51,238
What did he--

475
00:30:55,720 --> 00:30:57,915
That's right. Big Daddy is going to die.

476
00:31:01,040 --> 00:31:03,235
I don't believe that.

477
00:31:03,680 --> 00:31:06,513
Dr. Baugh wouldn't lie to Big Daddy.

478
00:31:06,720 --> 00:31:07,994
Wouldn't he, Maggie?

479
00:31:12,640 --> 00:31:14,596
Poor Big Daddy.

480
00:31:15,720 --> 00:31:17,551
I'm fond of him.

481
00:31:17,760 --> 00:31:20,354
I'm genuinely fond of that old man.

482
00:31:20,640 --> 00:31:22,517
I really am, you know.

483
00:31:23,960 --> 00:31:25,996
When he finds out....

484
00:31:26,960 --> 00:31:29,315
I wouldn't want to be the one to tell him.

485
00:31:31,600 --> 00:31:33,079
That's why you want to go now.

486
00:31:34,640 --> 00:31:37,108
Yeah, that's why I want to leave now.

487
00:31:39,720 --> 00:31:41,836
You've got to do this for me, Maggie.

488
00:31:42,040 --> 00:31:44,349
And leave the field to Gooper and his wife?

489
00:31:44,520 --> 00:31:45,475
No, sir!

490
00:31:45,680 --> 00:31:47,193
Let's face facts, baby.

491
00:31:47,400 --> 00:31:49,072
You're a drinker. That takes money.

492
00:31:49,280 --> 00:31:50,554
I don't want his money!

493
00:31:50,760 --> 00:31:52,671
Are you ready to settle for ten-cent beer?

494
00:31:52,760 --> 00:31:55,797
That's what Gooper'll dole out to you
when they freeze you out.

495
00:31:56,000 --> 00:31:58,150
They've got a plan, baby.

496
00:31:58,360 --> 00:32:02,672
You should've heard them
laying it on to Big Daddy. A mile a minute!

497
00:32:02,880 --> 00:32:05,314
Big Mama's already on their side.

498
00:32:05,800 --> 00:32:08,792
You're a drinker and I'm childless.

499
00:32:09,480 --> 00:32:12,916
We've got to beat that plan,
we've just got to!

500
00:32:15,840 --> 00:32:17,319
I've been so...

501
00:32:17,480 --> 00:32:20,517
...disgustingly poor all my life.

502
00:32:21,120 --> 00:32:23,315
That's the truth, Brick.

503
00:32:24,400 --> 00:32:26,277
Have you, Maggie?

504
00:32:26,400 --> 00:32:28,197
[Slow instrumental music]

505
00:32:28,320 --> 00:32:30,117
You don't know what it's like to have to...

506
00:32:30,240 --> 00:32:33,471
...suck up to people you can't stand,
just because they have money.

507
00:32:34,520 --> 00:32:36,590
You don't know what it's like...

508
00:32:36,800 --> 00:32:38,836
...never having any clothes.

509
00:32:39,800 --> 00:32:41,870
That dress I married you in...

510
00:32:42,080 --> 00:32:45,993
...was a hand-me-down
from a snotty, rich cousin I hated.

511
00:32:48,040 --> 00:32:50,270
You can be young without money.

512
00:32:51,400 --> 00:32:53,630
But you can't be old without it.

513
00:32:56,080 --> 00:32:58,150
Where did I fail you?

514
00:32:58,720 --> 00:33:00,950
Where did I make my mistake?

515
00:33:02,440 --> 00:33:04,670
Make that your last drink
until after the party...

516
00:33:04,760 --> 00:33:06,193
...please, honey.

517
00:33:12,840 --> 00:33:15,877
I think I made my mistake
when I tried to tell you about Skipper.

518
00:33:16,200 --> 00:33:17,997
-That's my fatal error.
-Maggie!

519
00:33:18,200 --> 00:33:20,316
-I never should--
-Shut up about Skipper!

520
00:33:20,520 --> 00:33:22,317
I mean it! Shut up!

521
00:33:22,520 --> 00:33:25,080
The laws of silence won't work about that!

522
00:33:25,280 --> 00:33:27,111
Not about Skipper and us.

523
00:33:27,320 --> 00:33:31,029
It's like locking the door on a fire
to forget the house is burning.

524
00:33:31,120 --> 00:33:32,473
BRlCK: Hey, everybody!

525
00:33:32,600 --> 00:33:33,669
[Thunder rumbles]

526
00:33:33,800 --> 00:33:36,792
MAGGlE: But not looking at a fire
doesn't put it out.

527
00:33:37,040 --> 00:33:41,670
This time I'm going to finish.
That night in the hotel room, Skipper--

528
00:33:41,760 --> 00:33:43,273
I don't want to hear about it!

529
00:33:43,520 --> 00:33:46,114
Why won't you face the truth, just once...

530
00:33:46,280 --> 00:33:49,317
...about Skipper, about me, about yourself?

531
00:33:49,400 --> 00:33:50,389
Hey, everybody!

532
00:33:50,520 --> 00:33:52,511
Are you bringing that party up here or not?

533
00:33:52,680 --> 00:33:54,477
BlG MAMA: Kit and caboodle, son.

534
00:33:54,680 --> 00:33:57,035
That won't do any good.
I'm going to say this...

535
00:33:57,240 --> 00:34:00,038
...and I don't care if it's in front of them.

536
00:34:01,720 --> 00:34:03,597
Do you want to be hit with this crutch?

537
00:34:03,680 --> 00:34:05,671
Are you still blaming me
for Skipper's death?

538
00:34:05,760 --> 00:34:07,352
I could kill you with this crutch.

539
00:34:07,560 --> 00:34:09,710
Good Lord! Do you think I'd care?

540
00:34:09,920 --> 00:34:12,753
Skipper and I had a friendship.
Why won't you let it alone?

541
00:34:12,840 --> 00:34:15,070
-It's got to be told!
-I don't want to hear it!

542
00:34:15,280 --> 00:34:18,511
It's got to be told
and you never let me tell it. I love you...

543
00:34:18,720 --> 00:34:21,359
...and that's worth fighting for.
Not Skipper!

544
00:34:21,560 --> 00:34:23,073
-Skipper was no good!
-Maggie!

545
00:34:23,280 --> 00:34:24,633
Maybe I'm no good.

546
00:34:24,840 --> 00:34:25,989
Nobody's good.

547
00:34:26,200 --> 00:34:28,475
But Skipper is dead!

548
00:34:28,840 --> 00:34:30,592
MAGGlE: And I'm alive!
BRlCK: Maggie!

549
00:34:30,760 --> 00:34:32,637
Maggie the cat is alive!

550
00:34:32,840 --> 00:34:34,159
I'm alive!

551
00:34:34,360 --> 00:34:36,271
Why are you afraid of the truth?

552
00:34:36,480 --> 00:34:37,469
Truth?

553
00:34:44,920 --> 00:34:48,595
Little girl, somebody ought to teach you...

554
00:34:48,800 --> 00:34:51,473
...to knock before you open a door.

555
00:34:51,680 --> 00:34:56,037
Otherwise, people might think
you're lacking in good breeding.

556
00:34:57,440 --> 00:34:59,431
Nyah nyah nyah!

557
00:34:59,520 --> 00:35:02,398
DlXlE: What's Uncle Brick doing
on the floor?

558
00:35:03,480 --> 00:35:05,630
I tried to kill your Aunt Maggie...

559
00:35:08,840 --> 00:35:10,114
...but I failed...

560
00:35:10,840 --> 00:35:14,674
...and I fell. Little girl,
would you hand me my crutch, please?

561
00:35:19,680 --> 00:35:22,513
DlXlE: What were you jumping
high hurdles for?

562
00:35:22,960 --> 00:35:26,669
Because I used to, and people like to do
what they used to do...

563
00:35:27,360 --> 00:35:29,954
...after they've stopped being able to do it.

564
00:35:30,120 --> 00:35:33,396
That's right. And that's your answer.

565
00:35:33,680 --> 00:35:34,795
Now go away.

566
00:35:36,160 --> 00:35:39,277
Stop that, you little no-neck monster!

567
00:35:39,480 --> 00:35:43,712
You're just jealous
because you can't have babies.

568
00:35:52,520 --> 00:35:53,714
You see?

569
00:35:55,200 --> 00:35:58,988
Mae and Gooper gloat over us
being childless...

570
00:36:00,280 --> 00:36:03,590
...even in front of their little
no-neck monsters.

571
00:36:09,000 --> 00:36:11,514
I went to a doctor in Memphis.

572
00:36:11,880 --> 00:36:13,950
A gynecologist.

573
00:36:15,080 --> 00:36:18,629
He says there's no reason
why we can't have a child...

574
00:36:18,840 --> 00:36:20,751
...whenever we want.

575
00:36:24,240 --> 00:36:25,275
Brick?

576
00:36:27,560 --> 00:36:30,916
-Are you listening?
-Yes, Maggie, I hear you.

577
00:36:32,320 --> 00:36:35,551
But how in hell do you imagine
you're going to have a child...

578
00:36:35,720 --> 00:36:38,234
...by a man who cannot stand you?

579
00:36:46,000 --> 00:36:48,036
That, boy of mine...

580
00:36:49,280 --> 00:36:52,590
...is a problem I'll just have to work out.

581
00:36:52,800 --> 00:36:55,189
Here comes that party, here we come!

582
00:36:55,400 --> 00:36:58,198
Here comes that birthday party!

583
00:36:58,480 --> 00:37:00,038
That's nice.

584
00:37:01,880 --> 00:37:03,472
DEACON: The preacher almost cried...

585
00:37:03,560 --> 00:37:06,199
...when I told him
I got a stained-glass memorial window.

586
00:37:06,280 --> 00:37:07,872
GOOPER: Who gave you that window?

587
00:37:07,960 --> 00:37:11,111
DEACON: Clyde Fletcher's widow,
a generous woman of fine character.

588
00:37:11,200 --> 00:37:13,839
What someone should give our church
is a cooling system.

589
00:37:13,920 --> 00:37:15,319
Yes, sir. Exactly my thought.

590
00:37:15,400 --> 00:37:18,790
Let's see, they've had the typhoid shots
and the tetanus shots...

591
00:37:19,000 --> 00:37:23,437
...diphtheria shots, hepatitis shots,
polio shots.

592
00:37:25,000 --> 00:37:27,912
MAE: Gooper, what have all the kiddies
been shot for?

593
00:37:28,120 --> 00:37:30,190
Everything but stealing chickens.

594
00:37:30,280 --> 00:37:31,759
[Laughter]

595
00:37:37,520 --> 00:37:38,509
Well, Brick?

596
00:37:39,200 --> 00:37:41,395
Congratulations, Big Daddy,
on your birthday.

597
00:37:41,600 --> 00:37:42,874
Bull!

598
00:37:42,960 --> 00:37:45,269
DEACON: Guess what memorial
Gus's family gave?

599
00:37:45,480 --> 00:37:47,948
-A new house and basketball court--
-Deacon!

600
00:37:48,840 --> 00:37:51,957
What's all this talk about
memorial stained-glass windows?

601
00:37:52,160 --> 00:37:54,913
Figuring on somebody kicking off
around here?

602
00:37:55,160 --> 00:37:58,755
How about some nice music
to start the party off with?

603
00:37:58,840 --> 00:38:00,831
[Classical music plays on radio]

604
00:38:02,320 --> 00:38:04,470
Turn that damn thing off!

605
00:38:06,440 --> 00:38:08,078
Where's my Brick?

606
00:38:08,160 --> 00:38:10,799
-Where's my precious baby?
-Sorry, turn it back on.

607
00:38:10,920 --> 00:38:13,070
BlG MAMA: How does your leg feel, honey?

608
00:38:13,160 --> 00:38:16,630
Your hand was made for holding
something better! Put that liquor down.

609
00:38:16,840 --> 00:38:19,991
GOOPER: He is putting it down, all right!
BlG MAMA: Turn that off!

610
00:38:20,080 --> 00:38:22,753
How about a birthday kiss, honey?

611
00:38:27,320 --> 00:38:31,996
Hey, everybody, you know the first time
Big Daddy kissed me, I fainted.

612
00:38:32,200 --> 00:38:34,077
It's a fact. Ain't that so, honey?

613
00:38:34,760 --> 00:38:38,673
Do you all know how he proposed to me?
I was four months swole with Gooper...

614
00:38:38,880 --> 00:38:41,917
...and Big Daddy said,
"That's my kid, ain't it?"

615
00:38:42,120 --> 00:38:44,350
It was kind of funny.
I'd never had a beau...

616
00:38:44,520 --> 00:38:47,159
...till I met your father.
He said, "I want that kid.

617
00:38:47,360 --> 00:38:48,588
"I need him.

618
00:38:48,800 --> 00:38:52,998
"He ain't going to have nobody else's name
but mine. Let's get the preacher.

619
00:38:53,160 --> 00:38:55,594
"That's what marriage is for. Family."

620
00:38:56,680 --> 00:38:59,399
Children were mighty important
to Big Daddy, even then.

621
00:38:59,560 --> 00:39:01,790
BlG DADDY: lda, will you stop
that yammering?

622
00:39:01,920 --> 00:39:04,832
That's just his manner of talking.
He don't mean it.

623
00:39:05,040 --> 00:39:07,679
I've been his one and only lover,
haven't l, sweetheart?

624
00:39:08,120 --> 00:39:09,951
BlG DADDY: lda, will you keep quiet?

625
00:39:10,880 --> 00:39:12,472
MAE: Children, come on!

626
00:39:12,600 --> 00:39:14,989
[Children murmur with excitement]

627
00:39:16,960 --> 00:39:19,952
BlG MAMA: Here comes
Big Daddy's birthday!

628
00:39:22,800 --> 00:39:25,633
MAE and CHlLDREN: [Sing]
"Big Daddy's a jolly good fellow

629
00:39:25,840 --> 00:39:28,149
"Big Daddy's a jolly good fellow

630
00:39:29,360 --> 00:39:31,828
"And so is Big Mama, too

631
00:39:38,000 --> 00:39:41,310
"Big Daddy's a jolly good fellow

632
00:39:42,400 --> 00:39:45,631
"And so is Big Mama, too"

633
00:39:47,640 --> 00:39:50,996
BlG DADDY: What's wrong with you?
MAE: She's just so happy.

634
00:39:51,880 --> 00:39:56,112
I'm so happy.
I've just got to cry or something.

635
00:39:57,000 --> 00:39:58,911
Big Daddy's 100 percent...

636
00:39:59,120 --> 00:40:00,189
...healthy!

637
00:40:00,320 --> 00:40:01,719
Brick, honey....

638
00:40:02,080 --> 00:40:04,674
Aren't you going to give Big Daddy
his birthday present?

639
00:40:09,040 --> 00:40:10,519
[Children squeal]

640
00:40:12,800 --> 00:40:15,155
BlG MAMA: You can open up
your birthday present.

641
00:40:15,240 --> 00:40:18,277
You open it. I want to talk to Brick.
Brick, come over here.

642
00:40:18,600 --> 00:40:20,750
Big Daddy's calling you.

643
00:40:20,960 --> 00:40:23,554
Big Mama, take them out for me.

644
00:40:23,760 --> 00:40:27,389
-It's a cashmere robe!
-You sound surprised.

645
00:40:27,600 --> 00:40:31,752
-I've never seen a cashmere robe before.
-That's funny!

646
00:40:32,480 --> 00:40:33,993
What's so funny about it?

647
00:40:34,600 --> 00:40:36,670
All my family ever had was family.

648
00:40:37,680 --> 00:40:38,749
Quiet!

649
00:40:38,960 --> 00:40:42,077
-You bought it yourself last Saturday.
-I said quiet!

650
00:40:42,280 --> 00:40:46,353
The salesgirl that sold it to you
waited on me and she told me about it.

651
00:40:46,560 --> 00:40:48,278
-Sister Woman!
-Quiet!

652
00:40:48,480 --> 00:40:50,835
-Stork and the Grim Reaper, neck and neck.
-Deacon!

653
00:40:50,920 --> 00:40:51,955
Deacon!

654
00:40:52,920 --> 00:40:57,277
I'm not butting in on more talk about
memorial stained-glass windows, am l?

655
00:40:57,760 --> 00:40:59,239
DEACON: Not at all.

656
00:41:00,200 --> 00:41:02,873
What do you get out
of this charity work, anyway?

657
00:41:03,760 --> 00:41:05,751
I love humanity. That's my reward.

658
00:41:05,960 --> 00:41:08,793
And if humanity returns your love,
you might get elected...

659
00:41:08,880 --> 00:41:10,632
...councilman or mayor, hey, Deacon?

660
00:41:10,840 --> 00:41:12,398
Don't start picking on Deacon.

661
00:41:12,480 --> 00:41:15,517
DEACON: That's all right. I was--
BlG DADDY: Good night, Deacon.

662
00:41:15,600 --> 00:41:19,275
That's exactly what I was about to say.
I better go before it starts raining.

663
00:41:19,360 --> 00:41:22,830
Good night, everybody.
Bless each and every one in this place.

664
00:41:24,040 --> 00:41:27,237
They tell me you were indulging in
some athletics last night.

665
00:41:27,440 --> 00:41:30,477
-I was trying to, yes, sir.
-At 3:00 in the morning?

666
00:41:30,920 --> 00:41:34,674
BlG DADDY: What were you doing on
the high school athletic field at 3:00 AM?

667
00:41:34,760 --> 00:41:39,356
I was running and jumping the hurdles.
They've got too high for me now.

668
00:41:39,640 --> 00:41:41,437
BlG DADDY: Because you were drunk!

669
00:41:41,520 --> 00:41:44,478
Sober, I would not have tried
to jump even the low ones.

670
00:41:44,840 --> 00:41:46,990
It's time to blow out the candles!

671
00:41:47,400 --> 00:41:49,834
MAGGlE: A toast to Big Daddy Pollitt...

672
00:41:50,040 --> 00:41:52,759
...on his 65th birthday.

673
00:41:52,960 --> 00:41:56,350
-To the biggest cotton planter--
-I told you, quit this bull!

674
00:41:56,480 --> 00:41:59,517
I won't let you talk this way,
not even on your birthday.

675
00:41:59,600 --> 00:42:03,149
BlG DADDY: I'll talk like I want to
on my birthday, or any other rotten day.

676
00:42:03,240 --> 00:42:06,038
Anybody don't like it,
they know what they can do about it.

677
00:42:06,120 --> 00:42:09,112
-I know you don't mean that.
-You don't know nothing, never did.

678
00:42:09,200 --> 00:42:12,715
BlG MAMA: You don't mean that.
BlG DADDY: Yes, I do mean it.

679
00:42:14,000 --> 00:42:17,913
I've put up with a lot of bull around here
because I thought I was dying.

680
00:42:18,120 --> 00:42:20,429
That's when you started taking over.

681
00:42:20,640 --> 00:42:24,838
Your loud voice and busybody butting in
here and there and everywhere.

682
00:42:25,000 --> 00:42:28,709
Sashaying around here,
making a big noise like a boss.

683
00:42:28,920 --> 00:42:31,309
I'm the only boss around here.

684
00:42:31,720 --> 00:42:34,598
I built this place with no help from you.

685
00:42:34,760 --> 00:42:37,638
And I'll run this place till the day I die.

686
00:42:37,840 --> 00:42:41,355
Is that plain to you, Ida?
Is that perfectly clear to you?

687
00:42:41,560 --> 00:42:42,709
I ain't going to die.

688
00:42:43,240 --> 00:42:46,277
Ain't nothing wrong with me
but a spastic colon!

689
00:42:46,840 --> 00:42:49,718
Made spastic, I reckon,
by all the lies and liars...

690
00:42:49,920 --> 00:42:52,229
...I've had to put up with around here.

691
00:42:52,440 --> 00:42:56,877
And all the hypocrisy I've had to live with
these 40 years I've lived with you.

692
00:42:57,960 --> 00:42:59,871
Now blow out them candles.

693
00:43:00,840 --> 00:43:03,798
Go on. Blow out them candles
on that stupid cake.

694
00:43:06,120 --> 00:43:08,111
[Softly] Oh, Big Daddy....

695
00:43:08,400 --> 00:43:12,871
In all these years
you never believed I loved you.

696
00:43:15,480 --> 00:43:16,959
And I did.

697
00:43:18,440 --> 00:43:20,192
I did so much.

698
00:43:21,320 --> 00:43:22,799
I did love you.

699
00:43:24,200 --> 00:43:28,079
I even loved your hate and your hardness.

700
00:43:28,880 --> 00:43:30,552
[Thunder rumbles]

701
00:43:34,120 --> 00:43:37,157
-Big Daddy should make plans.
-lf he should die before--

702
00:43:37,920 --> 00:43:39,194
DR. BAUGH: Excuse me.

703
00:43:42,120 --> 00:43:43,599
BlG DADDY: Brick!

704
00:43:44,280 --> 00:43:45,508
Son!

705
00:43:49,560 --> 00:43:51,232
BlG DADDY: I was calling Brick.

706
00:43:52,360 --> 00:43:54,794
I was just delivering him to you.

707
00:44:06,400 --> 00:44:09,039
BlG DADDY: What did you do that for?
BRlCK: Do what?

708
00:44:10,440 --> 00:44:11,873
Wipe off her kiss?

709
00:44:15,000 --> 00:44:16,115
Did l?

710
00:44:16,240 --> 00:44:18,629
BlG DADDY: Your woman's got
a better shape on her...

711
00:44:18,840 --> 00:44:20,353
...than Gooper's got on his.

712
00:44:20,880 --> 00:44:25,078
-ls that the only difference you've noticed?
-Difference in shape is pretty important.

713
00:44:25,280 --> 00:44:27,953
-But in a way, they're a lot alike.
-How's that?

714
00:44:28,160 --> 00:44:31,038
They don't look peaceful. How's that?

715
00:44:31,320 --> 00:44:33,276
They're a couple of cats...

716
00:44:33,520 --> 00:44:37,593
...sitting in the middle of 28,000 acres
of land. That's a lot of land.

717
00:44:37,960 --> 00:44:42,238
They're both squaring off, determined
to get a bigger piece whenever you let go.

718
00:44:43,120 --> 00:44:45,839
Yeah, well, I've got a surprise
for them babies.

719
00:44:46,040 --> 00:44:49,350
I ain't letting go for a long time yet,
if they're waiting for that.

720
00:44:49,440 --> 00:44:53,115
You just sit tight and let them
scratch each other's eyes out.

721
00:44:53,320 --> 00:44:54,673
You bet your life.

722
00:44:55,240 --> 00:44:58,869
Gooper's wife, she's a good breeder.
You'll have to admit she's fertile.

723
00:44:59,080 --> 00:45:01,469
Five head of them already
and more coming.

724
00:45:02,760 --> 00:45:06,036
6-0. She'll probably drop a litter next time.

725
00:45:08,160 --> 00:45:11,118
BlG DADDY: Are you stuck out there?
MAE: I was just passing by.

726
00:45:11,200 --> 00:45:13,031
You were just sneaking and spying.

727
00:45:13,120 --> 00:45:16,749
Do I have to lock all the doors around here
to have a private conversation?

728
00:45:16,960 --> 00:45:19,838
-Why hurt those that really love you?
-Bull!

729
00:45:20,080 --> 00:45:22,435
I'm going to move you and Gooper
out of that room.

730
00:45:22,600 --> 00:45:26,036
It's none of your business what goes on
in here between Brick and Maggie.

731
00:45:26,240 --> 00:45:28,800
I hate sneaking and spying!
It makes me puke!

732
00:45:33,720 --> 00:45:34,994
They listen, do they?

733
00:45:35,240 --> 00:45:36,992
Yeah, they listen.

734
00:45:37,200 --> 00:45:39,998
BlG DADDY: They run and tell Big Mama
everything they hear.

735
00:45:40,120 --> 00:45:43,669
They say Maggie sleeps on the bed
and you sleep on the sofa. Is that true?

736
00:45:44,080 --> 00:45:47,550
If you don't like Maggie, get rid of her!
What are you doing now?

737
00:45:47,640 --> 00:45:49,278
BRlCK: Freshening up my drink.

738
00:45:49,360 --> 00:45:52,272
BlG DADDY: You've a real liquor problem.
BRlCK: Yes, sir.

739
00:45:52,360 --> 00:45:54,999
BlG DADDY: Is that why you quit
sports announcing?

740
00:45:55,080 --> 00:45:57,230
BRlCK: I guess so. Yes, sir, that's it.

741
00:45:57,440 --> 00:45:59,317
Don't guess! It's too important!

742
00:45:59,840 --> 00:46:01,432
So you quit.

743
00:46:02,280 --> 00:46:04,953
-Some kind of a disappointment?
-I don't know. Do you?

744
00:46:05,040 --> 00:46:07,713
I'm asking you.
How should I know if you don't?

745
00:46:07,840 --> 00:46:09,319
[Big Daddy coughs]

746
00:46:12,040 --> 00:46:15,430
Do you think a shot of that whisky
would injure my spastic condition?

747
00:46:17,600 --> 00:46:18,828
No, sir.

748
00:46:20,000 --> 00:46:21,831
It might do it some good.

749
00:46:29,000 --> 00:46:31,070
The sky is open again, boy. It's open!

750
00:46:31,280 --> 00:46:33,032
BRlCK: That's the way to feel.

751
00:46:38,120 --> 00:46:39,838
I can breathe.

752
00:46:41,160 --> 00:46:43,833
All my life I've been like a doubled-up fist...

753
00:46:44,040 --> 00:46:46,759
...pounding and smashing and driving!

754
00:46:47,400 --> 00:46:50,073
But now I'm going
to take things easy with them.

755
00:46:51,880 --> 00:46:53,279
Do you know what I'm thinking?

756
00:46:53,360 --> 00:46:54,793
What's that, sir?

757
00:46:55,080 --> 00:46:56,195
Pleasure!

758
00:46:58,360 --> 00:47:01,830
I'll tell you, I still have a feeling for women,
and I'm 65.

759
00:47:02,040 --> 00:47:04,395
-That's mighty remarkable.
-Remarkable?

760
00:47:05,000 --> 00:47:05,955
Admirable.

761
00:47:06,160 --> 00:47:10,358
It's not only remarkable and admirable,
it's downright satisfying.

762
00:47:10,560 --> 00:47:13,472
-I'm going to have me a ball.
-A ball?

763
00:47:13,680 --> 00:47:15,398
I'm going to pick me a choice woman...

764
00:47:15,480 --> 00:47:19,189
...and I'm going to smother her in minks
and choke her with diamonds.

765
00:47:19,400 --> 00:47:21,118
I'm going to be happy!

766
00:47:23,360 --> 00:47:26,193
Why are you so restless?
You got ants in your britches?

767
00:47:26,280 --> 00:47:27,759
-Yes, sir.
-Why?

768
00:47:29,400 --> 00:47:31,868
-Something hasn't happened yet.
-What's that?

769
00:47:32,080 --> 00:47:34,469
-A click in my head.
-Did you say, "click"?

770
00:47:34,600 --> 00:47:38,354
Yes, sir. That click in my head
that makes me feel peaceful.

771
00:47:38,560 --> 00:47:40,630
Boy, sometimes you worry me.

772
00:47:41,960 --> 00:47:46,511
Like a switch clicking off in my head.
Turns the hot light off and the cool one on.

773
00:47:46,600 --> 00:47:48,397
All of a sudden, there's peace.

774
00:47:50,800 --> 00:47:52,916
You're a real alcoholic!

775
00:47:54,280 --> 00:47:55,554
That is the truth.

776
00:47:55,760 --> 00:47:59,548
Yes, sir, I am an alcoholic.
So, if you'll just excuse me.

777
00:47:59,680 --> 00:48:02,672
BlG DADDY: No, I won't!
BRlCK: I'm waiting for that click...

778
00:48:02,760 --> 00:48:06,514
...and I don't get it unless I'm alone!
I'm not talking. When it's quiet!

779
00:48:06,600 --> 00:48:10,639
You'll hear plenty of that in the grave.
Right now we're going to talk.

780
00:48:10,840 --> 00:48:14,150
This talk is like all the others.
It gets nowhere and it's painful!

781
00:48:15,120 --> 00:48:19,432
BlG DADDY: Let it be painful.
BRlCK: I can crawl and hop if I have to.

782
00:48:20,360 --> 00:48:25,434
If you aren't careful, you'll crawl out
this family and be drinking on skid row.

783
00:48:25,520 --> 00:48:27,112
Yeah, that will come too.

784
00:48:27,680 --> 00:48:31,514
No. Now that I'm straightened out,
I'm going to straighten you out.

785
00:48:31,600 --> 00:48:32,953
Sit down!

786
00:48:33,160 --> 00:48:36,914
It's no use. We talk in circles.
We have nothing to say to each other!

787
00:48:43,240 --> 00:48:46,232
BlG DADDY: Where are you going?
BRlCK: To get another bottle.

788
00:48:46,440 --> 00:48:48,749
BlG DADDY: No, you're not,
you drunken whelp!

789
00:48:50,520 --> 00:48:54,274
BlG MAMA: Why are you shouting?
I can't stand it!

790
00:48:54,480 --> 00:48:57,597
BlG DADDY: Get out of here!
Leave us alone! Why do you drink?

791
00:48:58,440 --> 00:49:01,238
BlG DADDY: You had better know
why you drink or give it up!

792
00:49:01,840 --> 00:49:03,068
Give me my crutch.

793
00:49:03,280 --> 00:49:04,076
Why do you drink?

794
00:49:04,160 --> 00:49:06,196
I stepped on that foot and now I'm in pain.

795
00:49:06,400 --> 00:49:07,628
Good!

796
00:49:07,840 --> 00:49:09,512
[Big Daddy moans]

797
00:49:11,200 --> 00:49:12,792
[Sound of breaking glass]

798
00:49:13,520 --> 00:49:16,080
BlG DADDY: [Groans]
At least you're not too numb...

799
00:49:16,160 --> 00:49:18,754
...with liquor to feel pain.

800
00:49:20,600 --> 00:49:22,591
-Why do you drink?
-Give me my crutch.

801
00:49:22,800 --> 00:49:25,837
-Tell me first.
-No, give me a drink first.

802
00:49:25,960 --> 00:49:27,439
Tell me first.

803
00:49:28,360 --> 00:49:31,193
-First you've got to tell me!
-All right! Disgust!

804
00:49:31,400 --> 00:49:34,392
-Disgust with what?
-You strike a hard bargain.

805
00:49:34,600 --> 00:49:39,037
-Boy, do you want liquor that bad?
-Yes, sir, I want liquor that bad.

806
00:49:39,160 --> 00:49:40,752
[Phone rings]

807
00:49:42,960 --> 00:49:45,076
What are you disgusted with?

808
00:49:45,840 --> 00:49:48,991
Mendacity! Do you know what that is?
It's lies and liars!

809
00:49:49,160 --> 00:49:51,355
Who's been lying to you? Maggie?

810
00:49:51,560 --> 00:49:53,790
No, not one lie or one person.
The whole thing.

811
00:49:53,960 --> 00:49:55,757
-You got a headache?
-No, I'm trying--

812
00:49:55,960 --> 00:49:59,669
Trying to concentrate, but you can't
because your brain is soaked with liquor.

813
00:49:59,880 --> 00:50:00,949
Wet brain!

814
00:50:01,960 --> 00:50:03,279
BlG DADDY: Mendacity!

815
00:50:03,480 --> 00:50:07,234
What do you know about mendacity?
I could write a book on it.

816
00:50:07,440 --> 00:50:11,149
-It's your sister calling from Memphis.
-To hell with her! Gooper?

817
00:50:11,240 --> 00:50:12,309
Get out of there!

818
00:50:12,680 --> 00:50:15,319
Go on. Close the door after you.

819
00:50:15,520 --> 00:50:16,350
Mendacity!

820
00:50:16,760 --> 00:50:21,436
Look at the lies I've got to put up with.
Pretenses, hypocrisy!

821
00:50:21,640 --> 00:50:25,918
Pretending like I care for Big Mama.
I haven't tolerated her in 40 years.

822
00:50:26,520 --> 00:50:30,195
Church! It bores me, but I go.

823
00:50:30,480 --> 00:50:34,758
All those swindling lodges, social clubs,
and money-grabbing auxiliaries...

824
00:50:34,920 --> 00:50:37,309
...that's got me on their number one
sucker list.

825
00:50:37,480 --> 00:50:41,519
Boy, I've lived with mendacity.
Why can't you live with it?

826
00:50:41,720 --> 00:50:46,396
You've got to. There's nothing to live with
but mendacity. Is there?

827
00:50:47,400 --> 00:50:49,470
Yes, sir, you can live with this.

828
00:50:52,360 --> 00:50:53,349
That's not living.

829
00:50:54,800 --> 00:50:57,792
-That's dodging away from life.
-I want to dodge away from it.

830
00:50:57,880 --> 00:50:59,393
Then why not kill yourself?

831
00:50:59,520 --> 00:51:01,112
BRlCK: Because I like to drink.

832
00:51:01,240 --> 00:51:02,753
I can't talk to you!

833
00:51:02,960 --> 00:51:04,075
BRlCK: I'm sorry.

834
00:51:04,200 --> 00:51:07,237
Do you expect me to turn over
28,000 acres of the richest land...

835
00:51:07,360 --> 00:51:09,954
-...this side of the Nile to a drunk fool?
-No, sir.

836
00:51:10,120 --> 00:51:13,317
I like you, son, but why should I subsidize
worthless behavior?

837
00:51:13,520 --> 00:51:15,272
BRlCK: Give it to Gooper and Mae.

838
00:51:15,480 --> 00:51:19,189
BlG DADDY: I can't stand Gooper and Mae
and those five screaming monkeys.

839
00:51:20,520 --> 00:51:23,159
I don't have to turn it over to any of you!

840
00:51:23,360 --> 00:51:27,273
To this day, I ain't made no will.
Now I don't have to, the pressure's off.

841
00:51:27,480 --> 00:51:30,119
I can wait and see
if you pull yourself together or not.

842
00:51:30,200 --> 00:51:31,394
BRlCK: That's right.

843
00:51:31,920 --> 00:51:35,310
BlG DADDY: I'm not kidding.
BRlCK: No, sir, I know you're not kidding.

844
00:51:35,720 --> 00:51:36,755
You don't care?

845
00:51:36,960 --> 00:51:38,916
No, sir, I don't care.

846
00:51:40,120 --> 00:51:41,712
Tell Lacey to drive me to the station.

847
00:51:41,800 --> 00:51:44,553
BlG DADDY: Now wait a minute!
BRlCK: Or I'll drive myself.

848
00:51:44,640 --> 00:51:46,232
I'm going home tonight. Now!

849
00:51:46,360 --> 00:51:48,669
-This is your home.
-ls it? Since when?

850
00:51:49,800 --> 00:51:51,711
Let's not leave it like this.

851
00:51:51,960 --> 00:51:54,428
Like all them other talks we've had.

852
00:51:54,640 --> 00:51:57,916
We always seem to talk around things.

853
00:51:58,280 --> 00:52:01,875
Seem to leave things unsaid and unspoken.

854
00:52:02,160 --> 00:52:05,550
-Now we've got to talk straight.
-It's too late for talk.

855
00:52:05,760 --> 00:52:06,829
Why?

856
00:52:07,040 --> 00:52:08,837
What are you disgusted about?

857
00:52:09,280 --> 00:52:11,999
Because you can't play football anymore?

858
00:52:12,360 --> 00:52:15,557
Because you lost your job?
I'll get it back for you!

859
00:52:15,680 --> 00:52:17,272
[Brick laughs]

860
00:52:21,320 --> 00:52:24,835
What? Sit in a glass box
watching games that I can't play?

861
00:52:25,040 --> 00:52:28,350
Describing what I can't do
while others do it?

862
00:52:29,520 --> 00:52:34,071
Filling my Coke with bourbon so I can
stand it? You'll get that back for me?

863
00:52:34,480 --> 00:52:36,550
I think you're passing the buck.

864
00:52:36,680 --> 00:52:38,159
[Thunder rumbles]

865
00:52:39,360 --> 00:52:40,679
Do you know many drinking men?

866
00:52:40,840 --> 00:52:42,353
I've known a good number.

867
00:52:42,560 --> 00:52:44,630
Could any of them they tell you
why they drank?

868
00:52:44,720 --> 00:52:46,358
You're passing the buck?

869
00:52:46,560 --> 00:52:50,235
You're passing the buck
to things like disgust and mendacity.

870
00:52:50,440 --> 00:52:52,510
If you've got to use that kind of language...

871
00:52:52,680 --> 00:52:55,717
...it's 90 proof bull and I ain't buying any!

872
00:52:55,880 --> 00:53:00,829
You started drinking with your friend
Skipper's death. Ain't that the truth?

873
00:53:00,960 --> 00:53:02,837
[Thunder rumbles]

874
00:53:09,560 --> 00:53:10,834
What are you suggesting?

875
00:53:11,880 --> 00:53:12,835
Nothing. But--

876
00:53:13,040 --> 00:53:14,268
But what?

877
00:53:14,440 --> 00:53:15,429
Say your mind.

878
00:53:15,800 --> 00:53:16,949
BRlCK: [Shouts] Say it!

879
00:53:17,040 --> 00:53:19,838
BlG DADDY: Why are you so excited?
BRlCK: Go ahead, say it!

880
00:53:19,960 --> 00:53:21,359
Why are you shouting like that?

881
00:53:21,440 --> 00:53:23,396
Skipper and I were friends, understand?

882
00:53:23,560 --> 00:53:24,993
Gooper said that Skipper was--

883
00:53:25,080 --> 00:53:27,913
Skipper is the only thing
that I've got left to believe in!

884
00:53:28,000 --> 00:53:29,592
And you drag it through the gutter!

885
00:53:29,680 --> 00:53:32,194
-Just a minute!
-You make it shameful and filthy!

886
00:53:41,760 --> 00:53:42,988
Give me your hand.

887
00:53:45,600 --> 00:53:48,876
I don't want your hand.
To hell with all lies and liars!

888
00:53:49,480 --> 00:53:52,040
BRlCK: Didn't you ever look up to anybody?

889
00:53:52,200 --> 00:53:53,918
Anybody at all in your whole life?

890
00:53:54,120 --> 00:53:56,839
Didn't you ever believe in anything,
anybody?

891
00:53:58,120 --> 00:54:00,873
No, sir, I guess you didn't.

892
00:54:01,200 --> 00:54:04,317
Nothing and nobody
except Big Daddy himself.

893
00:54:04,520 --> 00:54:06,511
You and Skipper played football together.

894
00:54:06,600 --> 00:54:09,160
Made a few touchdowns.
Does that make him God Almighty?

895
00:54:09,280 --> 00:54:10,269
I could depend on him.

896
00:54:10,360 --> 00:54:13,636
BlG DADDY: On the football field!
BRlCK: Anytime, anywhere, anyplace!

897
00:54:13,720 --> 00:54:15,836
BlG DADDY: Are you sure of that?
BRlCK: Yes.

898
00:54:15,960 --> 00:54:17,109
Bull!

899
00:54:17,240 --> 00:54:20,437
BlG DADDY:
Why did your big strong man fall apart?

900
00:54:21,000 --> 00:54:22,592
Why did Skipper crack up?

901
00:54:24,160 --> 00:54:25,388
All right.

902
00:54:26,520 --> 00:54:29,080
You're asking for it,
we're going to have that talk.

903
00:54:30,120 --> 00:54:32,429
That straight, true talk.

904
00:54:32,680 --> 00:54:34,113
It's too late to stop now.

905
00:54:34,320 --> 00:54:35,753
Can you say it without a drink?

906
00:54:35,840 --> 00:54:38,400
I haven't heard that mechanical click yet.

907
00:54:38,600 --> 00:54:42,593
You need a lot of crutches, don't you?
Clicks. Whisky.

908
00:54:42,800 --> 00:54:44,597
What else do you need?

909
00:54:44,800 --> 00:54:45,357
Skipper?

910
00:54:45,800 --> 00:54:48,189
BlG DADDY: He was a crutch for you too,
wasn't he?

911
00:54:48,320 --> 00:54:49,309
Yes, sir.

912
00:54:49,480 --> 00:54:51,994
I could lean on him, in school and out of it.

913
00:54:52,760 --> 00:54:56,355
How did Maggie take
this great and true friendship?

914
00:54:59,080 --> 00:54:59,910
Ask her.

915
00:55:00,120 --> 00:55:01,030
I'm asking you.

916
00:55:01,240 --> 00:55:04,596
If you want to know why Skipper
cracked up, ask Maggie the cat.

917
00:55:04,720 --> 00:55:06,199
BlG DADDY: What did she do?

918
00:55:06,320 --> 00:55:09,471
Chase him out of the window
of that Chicago hotel?

919
00:55:09,640 --> 00:55:13,110
Did that little bitty girl shove
your big hero out all by herself?

920
00:55:13,760 --> 00:55:14,795
Why?

921
00:55:15,880 --> 00:55:17,950
What went on
between Skipper and Maggie?

922
00:55:19,360 --> 00:55:20,236
Ask her.

923
00:55:22,040 --> 00:55:23,519
[Thunder rumbles]

924
00:55:25,200 --> 00:55:26,679
BlG DADDY: Maggie, come here.

925
00:55:26,760 --> 00:55:29,354
MAE: Can I be of assistance, Big Daddy?

926
00:55:32,800 --> 00:55:35,234
Trixie's ready to play the piano for you!

927
00:55:35,440 --> 00:55:37,590
Go ahead, play.

928
00:55:37,720 --> 00:55:39,711
[Plays halting musical scale]

929
00:55:45,280 --> 00:55:48,192
What was going on
between you and Skipper?

930
00:55:50,120 --> 00:55:52,031
Well, you see, Big Daddy....

931
00:55:53,960 --> 00:55:55,109
Well?

932
00:55:56,320 --> 00:55:58,117
Come on, Maggie!

933
00:55:58,320 --> 00:56:00,356
You wanted to talk truth upstairs.

934
00:56:00,520 --> 00:56:01,953
Go ahead!

935
00:56:02,120 --> 00:56:04,680
Big Daddy wants to know. Tell him!

936
00:56:09,800 --> 00:56:11,472
MAGGlE: Skipper didn't like me.

937
00:56:11,680 --> 00:56:13,636
BRlCK: Why didn't Skipper like you?

938
00:56:13,840 --> 00:56:16,400
-You know he was against our marriage.
-Why?

939
00:56:16,600 --> 00:56:20,195
-Because it meant less freedom for you.
-Freedom to do what?

940
00:56:20,360 --> 00:56:22,794
Freedom to run from town to town.

941
00:56:23,000 --> 00:56:25,150
Planes, trains, always running!

942
00:56:25,320 --> 00:56:29,438
-Football practice, dirty stories--
-Nobody forced you to come along with us!

943
00:56:29,640 --> 00:56:33,349
I didn't expect to spend my honeymoon
in the locker room with the boys.

944
00:56:33,560 --> 00:56:37,030
BRlCK: Since when did a man's smell
ever injure your sensitive feelings?

945
00:56:37,240 --> 00:56:38,673
Football, baby!

946
00:56:38,880 --> 00:56:41,155
The idea of football smelled.

947
00:56:41,320 --> 00:56:44,153
Especially the notions
of a professional team.

948
00:56:44,360 --> 00:56:46,510
He didn't need any team of his own.

949
00:56:46,720 --> 00:56:50,076
He could've gotten a spot
on any pro team in the country.

950
00:56:51,080 --> 00:56:53,469
You organized your own team
on account of Skipper.

951
00:56:53,680 --> 00:56:54,908
BRlCK: You're a liar!

952
00:56:55,000 --> 00:56:57,036
He wasn't good enough on his own.

953
00:56:57,240 --> 00:56:59,470
Professional football is a business...

954
00:56:59,680 --> 00:57:00,669
...not a social club!

955
00:57:01,360 --> 00:57:03,316
You mean the business of making money?

956
00:57:03,520 --> 00:57:05,988
Yeah, money!
The stuff your dreams are made of!

957
00:57:06,480 --> 00:57:09,153
The Dixie Stars never made a nickel!

958
00:57:09,320 --> 00:57:11,629
Not from the first day to the last.

959
00:57:11,840 --> 00:57:13,876
It wasn't the money, it was the cheers.

960
00:57:14,080 --> 00:57:15,479
He lapped them up.

961
00:57:15,680 --> 00:57:19,150
The cheers didn't mean anything to me.
But they did to you!

962
00:57:19,360 --> 00:57:22,079
Because they shut you out
and you hated that.

963
00:57:22,280 --> 00:57:24,475
Not by the crowds, baby, by you.

964
00:57:24,680 --> 00:57:26,398
By the man I worshiped.

965
00:57:26,600 --> 00:57:28,875
That's why I hated Skipper.

966
00:57:29,600 --> 00:57:33,115
You hated him so much you got him drunk
and went to bed with him.

967
00:57:43,560 --> 00:57:45,312
Is that true?

968
00:57:50,240 --> 00:57:51,912
Oh, Big Daddy....

969
00:57:52,720 --> 00:57:56,429
You don't think I ravished a football hero?

970
00:57:59,560 --> 00:58:01,152
Skipper was drunk.

971
00:58:01,600 --> 00:58:03,511
So are you most of the time.

972
00:58:03,720 --> 00:58:06,359
I don't seem to make out so well with you.

973
00:58:07,880 --> 00:58:09,677
[lncredulously] Are you....

974
00:58:10,360 --> 00:58:13,432
Are you saying nothing happened
between you and Skipper?

975
00:58:13,560 --> 00:58:16,120
MAGGlE: You know what happened.
BRlCK: I don't know!

976
00:58:16,320 --> 00:58:18,072
I wasn't there.

977
00:58:18,280 --> 00:58:21,033
I couldn't play that Sunday.
I wasn't in Chicago.

978
00:58:21,240 --> 00:58:23,196
-I was in the hospital--
-Skipper played.

979
00:58:23,280 --> 00:58:24,633
He played all right!

980
00:58:24,840 --> 00:58:26,956
