Skipper fumbled...

986
00:58:42,240 --> 00:58:44,674
...and stumbled and fell apart.

987
00:58:45,000 --> 00:58:48,879
On offensive he was useless.
On defensive he was a coward.

988
00:58:49,080 --> 00:58:50,433
And it was all over:

989
00:58:50,600 --> 00:58:53,512
Chicago: 47, Dixie Stars: 0.

990
00:58:53,720 --> 00:58:55,278
Bad breaks. An off day.

991
00:58:55,360 --> 00:58:56,429
MAGGlE: No, baby.

992
00:58:56,840 --> 00:58:59,559
Without you, Skipper was nothing.

993
00:58:59,720 --> 00:59:01,790
Outside: big, tough, confident.

994
00:59:01,960 --> 00:59:03,791
Inside: pure jelly!

995
00:59:04,840 --> 00:59:07,195
You saw the game on TV.
You saw what happened.

996
00:59:07,400 --> 00:59:09,994
But I didn't see what happened
in Skipper's hotel room.

997
00:59:10,080 --> 00:59:11,911
That little episode was not on TV.

998
00:59:12,120 --> 00:59:15,192
Tell Big Daddy
why you were in Skipper's room.

999
00:59:15,400 --> 00:59:16,719
He was sick.

1000
00:59:17,120 --> 00:59:18,519
Sick with drink.

1001
00:59:18,720 --> 00:59:19,948
He wouldn't come out.

1002
00:59:20,040 --> 00:59:21,359
He'd busted some furniture...

1003
00:59:21,440 --> 00:59:25,069
...and the hotel manager said to stop him
before he called the police.

1004
00:59:25,320 --> 00:59:27,515
So I went to his room.

1005
00:59:27,800 --> 00:59:30,394
I scratched on his door
and begged him to let me in.

1006
00:59:30,600 --> 00:59:31,919
He was half crazy.

1007
00:59:32,120 --> 00:59:33,712
Violent and screaming one minute...

1008
00:59:33,920 --> 00:59:36,115
...weak and crying the next.

1009
00:59:36,320 --> 00:59:39,676
And all the time, scared stiff about you.

1010
00:59:40,520 --> 00:59:44,195
So I said to him maybe it was time
we forgot about football.

1011
00:59:44,680 --> 00:59:47,990
Maybe he ought to get a job
and let me and Brick alone.

1012
00:59:49,120 --> 00:59:51,509
I thought he'd hit me.

1013
00:59:52,560 --> 00:59:54,391
He walked toward me...

1014
00:59:54,800 --> 00:59:58,509
...with a funny sort of smile on his face.

1015
00:59:59,960 --> 01:00:02,349
Then he did the strangest thing.

1016
01:00:02,720 --> 01:00:04,438
He kissed me.

1017
01:00:05,080 --> 01:00:07,548
